</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB1395:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB1395"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              1395-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 1395</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Harabedian<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 21, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to amend Section 4428 of the Public Resources Code, relating to forestry. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 1395, as introduced, Harabedian.
                          Forestry: internal combustion engines: industrial operations: fire toolbox.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law prohibits any person, except as specified, from using or operating any vehicle, machine, tool, or equipment powered by an internal combustion engine operated on hydrocarbon fuels, in any industrial operation located on or near any forest, brush, or grass-covered land between April 1 and December 1 of any year, or at any other time when ground litter and vegetation will sustain combustion permitting the spread of fire, without providing and maintaining, for firefighting purposes only, suitable and serviceable tools, as prescribed. Existing law requires a sealed box of tools, containing specified items, including one backpack pump-type fire extinguisher filled with water, to be located within the operating area and accessible in the event of a fire.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would instead require a dedicated set of tools, as specified, including a
		sufficient number of fire extinguishers, to be located within the operating area and accessible in the event of a fire, so that, when added to any other tools on the industrial operation, each employee at the operation can be equipped to fight fire. The bill would make other nonsubstantive changes to these provisions.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.29234678516613855"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 4428 of the Public Resources Code is amended to read:</div><div><div id="id_7E9E3AD3-4245-41A9-A9BB-80DF1074614F"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">4428.</h6> <font color="#B30000"><strike>No </strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(a) A </i></font>person, except<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> member of an emergency crew or except the driver or owner of<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> service vehicle owned or operated by or for, or operated under contract with, a publicly or privately owned<font color="#B30000"><strike> utility, which</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
				  utility that</i></font> is used in the construction, operation, removal, or repair of the property or facilities of<font color="#B30000"><strike> such</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> the</i></font> utility when engaged in emergency operations, shall<font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> not</i></font> use or operate<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> vehicle, machine,<font color="#B30000"><strike> tool</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> tool,</i></font> or equipment powered by an internal combustion engine operated on hydrocarbon<font color="#B30000"><strike> fuels,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> fuels</i></font> in<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> an</i></font> industrial operation located on or near<font color="#B30000"><strike> any</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> a</i></font> forest, brush, or grass-covered land between April 1 and December 1 of any year, or at any other time when ground litter and vegetation will sustain combustion permitting the spread of fire, without providing and maintaining, for firefighting purposes only, suitable and serviceable tools in the amounts,<font color="#B30000"><strike> manner</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> manner,</i></font> and location prescribed in this section.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(a)<span class="EnSpace"/>On any such operation  an</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(b) On an industrial operation,</i></font> a<font color="#B30000"><strike> sealed box</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> dedicated set</i></font> of tools shall be<font color="#B30000"><strike> located,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> located</i></font> within the operating area, at a point accessible in the event of fire. This fire toolbox shall<font color="#B30000"><strike> contain: one backpack pump-type</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> contain a sufficient number of</i></font> fire<font color="#B30000"><strike> extinguisher filled with water, two</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> extinguishers,</i></font> axes,<font color="#B30000"><strike> two</strike></font> McLeod fire tools, and<font color="#B30000"><strike> a sufficient number of shovels so that</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> shovels, so that when added to any other tools on the operation,</i></font> each employee at the operation can be equipped to fight fire.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(b)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(c)</i></font> One or more serviceable chainsaws of three and one-half or more horsepower with a cutting bar 20 inches in length or longer shall be immediately available within the operating area, or, in the alternative, a full set of timber-felling tools shall be located in the fire<font color="#B30000"><strike> toolbox,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> toolbox described in subdivision (b),</i></font> including one crosscut falling saw six feet in length, one double-bit ax with a 36-inch handle, one sledge hammer or maul with a head weight of<font color="#B30000"><strike> six,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> six</i></font> or<font color="#B30000"><strike> more,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> more</i></font> pounds and handle length of 32<font color="#B30000"><strike> inches,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> inches</i></font> or more, and not less than two falling wedges.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(c)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(d)</i></font> Each rail speeder and passenger<font color="#B30000"><strike> vehicle,</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> vehicle</i></font> used on<font color="#B30000"><strike> such</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> the</i></font> operation shall be equipped with one shovel and one ax, and any other vehicle used on the operation shall be equipped with one shovel. Each tractor used<font color="#B30000"><strike> in such</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> on the</i></font> operation shall be equipped with one shovel.</div><font color="#B30000"><strike><p style="display:inline;"><s>(d)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(e)</i></font> As used in this<font color="#B30000"><strike> section:</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> section, the following terms shall apply:</i></font></div><font color="#B30000"><strike><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(1)<span class="EnSpace"/>“Vehicle” means a device by which any person or property may be propelled, moved, or drawn over any land surface, excepting a device
				  moved by human power or used exclusively upon stationary rails or tracks.</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div><s><p style="margin-left: 1em;">(2)</s></p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"></div></strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1)</i></font> “Passenger vehicle” means a vehicle<font color="#B30000"><strike> which</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> that</i></font> is<font color="#B30000"><strike> self-propelled and which is</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> self-propelled,</i></font> designed for carrying not more than 10 persons including the driver, and<font color="#B30000"><strike> which is</strike></font> used or maintained for the transportation of persons, but does not include any motortruck or truck tractor.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) “Vehicle” means a device by which any person or property may be propelled, moved, or drawn over any land surface, excepting a device moved by human power or used exclusively upon stationary rails or tracks.</div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
